==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[abbreviatus]]'', past participle of ''[[abbreviare]]'', formed from ''[[ad-]]'' + ''[[breviare]]'' "to shorten", from ''[[brevis]]'' short.

===Pronunciation===
* ''[[RP]]:''
** {{IPA|/əˈbriːvieɪt/}}

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|abbreviat|e|}}

# {{transitive}} To make [[short]]er; to [[shorten]]; to [[abridge]]; to reduce by means of [[contraction]] or [[omission]], especially of [[word]]s written or spoken.
#* It is one thing to ''abbreviate'' by contracting, another by cutting off. — Bacon
# {{math}} To [[reduce]] to lower terms, as a [[fraction]].

====Related terms====
* [[abbreviation]]
* [[abbreviator]]

